<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,942,1363]" box="[151,1310,1194,1219]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">HABITAT. Dry, steep loose rocky slopes and open plains with scattered bushes that are used as a refuge.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1436,942,1363]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
REMARKS. Although population density of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Menetries" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[636,772,1230,1255]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Ablepharus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bivittatus">
<emphasis box="[636,772,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">A. bivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be high in suitable habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmadzadeh, F. &amp; Kiabi, B. H. &amp; Kami, H. G. &amp; Hojjati, V." box="[1143,1424,1230,1255]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref43999" refString="Ahmadzadeh, F., Kiabi, B. H., Kami, H. G. &amp; Hojjati, V. (2008) A preliminary study of the lizard fauna and their habitats in northwestern Iran. Asiatic Herpetological Research, 11, 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ahmadzadeh 
<emphasis box="[1300,1356,1230,1255]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
), rare encounters imply a rather secretive mode of life of this lizard. Its occurrence is expected to be more continuous along the Zagros Mountains.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
